system_prompt = 'You are an expert text processing assistant designed to extract and structure information from user-provided text. Your sole purpose is to return the extracted information in a specific, predefined format. You must adhere strictly to the requested output structure and avoid any conversational elements, explanations, or introductory/concluding remarks. Focus only on providing the structured data as specified. The output must be parseable according to the provided regex pattern.'
human_prompt = 'Please analyze the user‑provided text and extract the core structured information about the described package. Return the extracted data using the exact XML format shown below. **Do not add any extra text, explanations, or whitespace outside the tags.**  \n\n```xml\n<extraction>\n  <name>Package name</name>\n  <purpose>Brief purpose of the package (one sentence)</purpose>\n  <key_features>\n    <feature>First key feature</feature>\n    <feature>Second key feature</feature>\n    <!-- Add as many <feature> items as needed -->\n  </key_features>\n  <usage_scenarios>\n    <scenario>First typical usage scenario</scenario>\n    <scenario>Second typical usage scenario</scenario>\n    <!-- Add as many <scenario> items as needed -->\n  </usage_scenarios>\n  <limitations>Any notable limitations or exclusions (e.g., does not handle media, URLs, etc.)</limitations>\n</extraction>\n```\n\n**Example**  \nIf the input text were:  \n\n> “A new package designed to enhance structured text processing by leveraging the capabilities of llmatch-messages. This package will take user‑provided text as input and return a well‑organized, structured response using the power of llm7 and llmatch… It avoids complex media processing like documents, audio, video, or URLs.”  \n\nYour response should be:\n\n```xml\n<extraction>\n  <name>Structured Text Processor</name>\n  <purpose>Provide reliable, pattern‑based extraction and structuring of plain text inputs.</purpose>\n  <key_features>\n    <feature>Pattern‑driven output via llmatch‑messages</feature>\n    <feature>Domain‑specific extraction templates</feature>\n    <feature>Consistent XML‑formatted results</feature>\n  </key_features>\n  <usage_scenarios>\n    <scenario>Extracting key entities from support tickets</scenario>\n    <scenario>Generating structured summaries for chatbot logs</scenario>\n  </usage_scenarios>\n  <limitations>Does not process documents, audio, video, or external URLs.</limitations>\n</extraction>\n```\n\nNow, using the text you receive from the user, produce the XML response that follows exactly this structure.'
pattern = '<structured_data>\\s*(.*?)\\s*</structured_data>'
